#Removes the first occurrence of the specified element from the list, if it exists. They are:
 -remove(Object): Removes the first occurrence of the specified object from the LinkedList.
 -remove(int index): Removes the element at the given index and shifts subsequent elements.
 -removeFirst(): Removes the first element from the LinkedList.
 -removeLast(): Removes the last element from the LinkedList.
 -removeFirstOccurrence(Object o): Removes the first occurrence of the specified object from the LinkedList.
 -removeLastOccurrence(Object o): Removes the last occurrence of the specified object from the LinkedList.
 -clear(): Removes all the elements from the LinkedList.


